LLVM.AST.Operand

Description

A type to represent operands to LLVM Instructions

    • | PointerType
    • | PtrToMemberType
    • | ReferenceType
    • | RValueReferenceType
    • | ConstType
    • | VolatileType
    • | RestrictType
    • | AtomicType
    • | Member
    • | Inheritance
    • | Friend

    • | UnspecifiedType
  • data Virtuality
    • = NoVirtuality
    • | Virtual
    • | PureVirtual
  • data DISubprogram = Subprogram {
    • scope :: Maybe (MDRef DIScope)
    • name :: ShortByteString
    • linkageName :: ShortByteString
    • file :: Maybe (MDRef DIFile)
    • line :: Word32
    • type' :: Maybe (MDRef DISubroutineType)

    • definition :: Bool
    • scopeLine :: Word32
    • containingType :: Maybe (MDRef DIType)
    • virtuality :: Virtuality
    • virtualityIndex :: Word32
    • thisAdjustment :: Int32
    • flags :: [DIFlag]
    • optimized :: Bool
    • unit :: Maybe (MDRef DICompileUnit)

    • declaration :: Maybe (MDRef DISubprogram)
    • retainedNodes :: [MDRef DILocalVariable]
    • thrownTypes :: [MDRef DIType]
    }

  • data ChecksumKind
    • = MD5
    • | SHA1

    }

    • attributes :: Word32

    }
  • data DINode
    • = DIEnumerator DIEnumerator

    • | DISubrange DISubrange
    • | DITemplateParameter DITemplateParameter
    • | DIVariable DIVariable
  • data DIMacroNode
    • = DIMacro {
      • info :: DIMacroInfo
      • line :: Word32
      • name :: ShortByteString
      • value :: ShortByteString
      }
    • | DIMacroFile {
      • line :: Word32
      • file :: MDRef DIFile
      • elements :: [MDRef DIMacroNode]
      }
  • data DIMacroInfo
    • = Define
    • | Undef
  • data DIFlag
    • = Accessibility DIAccessibility
    • | FwdDecl
    • | AppleBlock
    • | BlockByrefStruct
    • | VirtualFlag
    • | Artificial
    • | Explicit
    • | Prototyped
    • | ObjcClassComplete
    • | ObjectPointer
    • | Vector
    • | StaticMember
    • | LValueReference
    • | RValueReference
    • | InheritanceFlag DIInheritance
    • | IntroducedVirtual
    • | BitField
    • | NoReturn
    • | MainSubprogram
  • data DIInheritance
    • = SingleInheritance
    • | MultipleInheritance
    • | VirtualInheritance
  • data DIAccessibility
    • = Private
    • | Protected
    • | Public
  • data DIGlobalVariableExpression = GlobalVariableExpression {
    • var :: MDRef DIGlobalVariable
    • expr :: MDRef DIExpression
    }
  • data DIExpression = Expression {
    • operands :: [DWOp]
    }
  • data DILocation = Location {
    • line :: Word32
    • column :: Word16
    • scope :: MDRef DILocalScope
    }
  • data MDNode
    • = MDTuple [Maybe Metadata]
    • | DIExpression DIExpression
    • | DIGlobalVariableExpression DIGlobalVariableExpression
    • | DILocation DILocation
    • | DIMacroNode DIMacroNode
    • | DINode DINode
  • data DWOp
    • = DwOpFragment DWOpFragment
    • | DW_OP_StackValue
    • | DW_OP_Swap
    • | DW_OP_ConstU Word64
    • | DW_OP_Lit0
    • | DW_OP_PlusUConst Word64
    • | DW_OP_Plus
    • | DW_OP_Minus
    • | DW_OP_Mul
    • | DW_OP_Div
    • | DW_OP_Mod
    • | DW_OP_Not
    • | DW_OP_Or
    • | DW_OP_Xor
    • | DW_OP_And
    • | DW_OP_Shr
    • | DW_OP_Shra
    • | DW_OP_Shl
    • | DW_OP_Dup
    • | DW_OP_Deref
    • | DW_OP_XDeref
  • data DWOpFragment = DW_OP_LLVM_Fragment {
    • offset :: Word64
    • size :: Word64
    }
  • data MDRef a
    • = MDRef MetadataNodeID
    • | MDInline a
  • newtype MetadataNodeID = MetadataNodeID Word
  • data Metadata
    • = MDString ShortByteString
    • | MDNode (MDRef MDNode)
    • | MDValue Operand
  • type CallableOperand = Either InlineAssembly Operand
  • data Operand
    • = LocalReference Type Name
    • | ConstantOperand Constant
    • | MetadataOperand Metadata

data MDRef a Source #

MDRef can either represent a reference to some piece of metadata or the metadata itself.

This is mainly useful for encoding cyclic metadata. Note that LLVM represents inline and non-inline nodes identically, so roundtripping the Haskell AST does not preserve whether a node was inline or not.
